item.title: 【Singles (lossless)】FLAC - Take That - It Only Takes A Minute (Remixes) [CD/WEB 44100kHz 16bit]
item.description:
CD rips & cleaned-by-me vinyl transfers that I've collected over the years. This is all the official versions & best remixes I could find on Discogs. If I'm missing anything, let me know so I can track it down.

Decode at https://www.base64decode.org/

* the name of this remix is actually unknown, it's a cd rip of the version on Hot Tracks 12-4 compilation, only remixer name given "Ron Hester". The real "Royal Rave Mix" (aka the "Dub" mix in a few different single issues) is actually a poorly-done instrumental mixdown of the original multitrack and contains an awful "crowd" track from start to finish. But I've provided a far better version here, so I gave the name to a much-worthier remix.

** the real "Dub Mix" is also known as the Royal Rave Mix/Wright Vocal Dub and it's terrible, as explained above. So I remastered it from scratch & produced a far better and cleaner instrumental.

*** the "Blondapella" is a slower & shorter version of the acappella that ends after the second chorus. Here is a remastered-by-me and complete version that follows the album mix.
